  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of online discourse and citation activity, \"Migratie in Belgi\u00eb in 21 vragen en antwoorden\" published by Leuven University Press in 2018 demonstrates solid attributes regarding commercial linkage, with notable presence on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, indicating potential engagement with a broader audience.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2018 by Leuven University Press, \"Migratie in Belgi\u00eb in 21 vragen en antwoorden\" aims to provide accessible insights into migration in Belgium through a question-and-answer format. While the book has yet to achieve scholarly citations, its commercial linkage is noteworthy, with a significant presence on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads. This suggests that the book may serve not only an academic audience but also a larger public interested in migration issues.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The content of the book is particularly relevant in the context of discussions around migration and policy in Belgium, reflecting a timely need for comprehensive resources. Although there has been no documentation of community discourse on popular digital platforms, the approach of addressing this critical subject through frequent questions and detailed answers could foster engagement once it reaches a wider audience.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book's inferred role in sustainability and policy, with a strength of 0.55, indicates some alignment with broader societal concerns, which aligns with a global emphasis on sustainable development goals. This connection could be leveraged for future outreach efforts, potentially translating the book's themes into actionable policies or educational programs.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, while \"Migratie in Belgi\u00eb in 21 vragen en antwoorden\" currently lacks extensive academic visibility, its commercial viability and relevance to policy discussions suggest that it holds promise for future influence, both academically and within public discourse on migration. Evaluating its impact may require time and further outreach to engage effectively with both scholars and practitioners in the field.</p>",
